definition.value: A copolymer comprising molecules with one or more species of block connected to the main chain as side chains. The side chains contain at least one different species of monomer to the main chain.
A copolymer consisting of macromolecules comprising more than two species of monomeric units in regular sequence.
A copolymer consisting of macromolecules in which the probability of finding a given monomeric unit at any given site in the chain is independent of the nature of the adjacent units.
A macromolecule with regularity or symmetry in the structural arrangement of its monomers.
A copolymer composed of 2-hydroxyethyl 2-methylpropanoate and propanoic acid units.
A polymer composed of repeating 2-[(E)-2-(3-ethenylphenyl)ethenyl]-1,4-bis(octyloxy)benzene units.
A copolymer composed of 2-methylpropanoic acid and ethylbenzene units.
Thymidine linked to the radioisotope tritium. Used to label DNA in the study of cellular and viral DNA synthesis.
A tritiated thymidine having the tritium label on the methyl group of the nucleobase.

A biflavonoid that is the  7,4'-dimethyl ether derivative of amentoflavone. Isolated from Ginkgo biloba and Dioon, it exhibits anti-HSV-1, antineoplastic and inhibitory activities towards arachidonate 5-lipoxygenase and cyclooxygenase 2.
The 7-hydroxy derivative of (3E)-6-methylhepta-3,5-dien-2-one.
A macromolecule composed of repeating L-arginyl units joined via peptide linkages.
A macromolecule composed of repeating D-arginyl units joined via peptide linkages.
A macromolecule composed of repeating oxyalkylene units.
An acrylate macromolecule, composed of repeating 2-hydroxyethyl 2-methylpropanoate units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating arginyl units joined via peptide linkages.
A diblock copolymer composed of methylene and ethyl benzene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating ethene units.
A poly(ethylene glycol) terminated with -NH2 groups.
A hydrate of nickel chloride containing nickel (in the +2 oxidation state), chloride and water moeities in the ratio 1:2:6.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 2-ethoxyethanol units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 5-(4-benzoylphenoxy)-2-hydroxybenzenesulfonic acid units.
A diblock copolymer composed of adjacent blocks of poly(oxyethylene) and polystyrene.
A diblock copolymer composed of adjacent blocks of polystyrene and poly(acrylic acid).
A deoxyhexitol compound with the 2-hydroxy substituent either absent or replaced by a different functional group.

A tripartite compound comprising an alpha-D-Gal unit linked to beta-D-GlcNAc, which is in turn linked to a CETE (2-[(2-carbomethoxyethylthio)]ethyl; 2-{[2-(methoxycarbonyl)ethylsulfanyl]}ethyl) moiety.

A branched pentasaccharide comprising a linear chain of alpha-L-fucosyl, beta-D-glucosaminyl, beta-D-galactosyl and alpha-D-glucose residues linked sequentially (1->4), (1->3) and (1->4), to the glucosaminyl residue of which is also linked (1->3) an alpha-D-galactosyl residue.
A polymer compose of repeating propane-1,2-diyl units.
A polymer composed of repeating CH2 units.
An imidazoline that is 4,5-dihydroimidazole bearing a chloromethyl substituent at position 2.
A hydrochloride salt having 2-(chloromethyl)-4,5-dihydro-1H-imidazole as the basic component.
The monoazo compound formed from arsanilic acid. It is used as an immunologic research tool.
A diisocyanate that consists of toluene bearing two isocyanato functional groups positioned meta to one another.
A toluene meta-diisocyanate in which the isocyanato groups are at positions 2 and 4 relative to the methyl group on the benzene ring.
A toluene meta-diisocyanate in which the isocyanato groups are at positions 2 and 6 relative to the methyl group on the benzene ring.
The hydrochloride salt of D-lysine.

A topoisomerase inhibitor that inhibits DNA topoisomerase IV, which catalyses ATP-dependent breakage of both strands of DNA, passage of the unbroken strands through the breaks, and rejoining of the broken strands.

A ginkgolide in which the pro-R hydrogens at positions 6, 12, and 17 of the  8-tert-butyl-16-methyl-2,4,14,19-tetraoxahexacyclo[8.7.2.0(1,11).0(3,7).0(7,11).0(13,17)]nonadecane-5,15,18-trione ginkgolide skeleton have been replaced by hydroxy groups.
The (R)-enantiomer of gatifloxacin.
The (S)-enantiomer of gatifloxacin.
A polymer composed of repeating 1-(4-iodophenyl)ethylene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 1-vinylethylene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating methyl(3-sulfanylpropyl)siloxane units.
An acrylate macromolecule, composed of repeating 2-(2-methoxyethoxy)ethyl 2-methylpropanoate units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating phenylenediethylene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating p-phenylenediethylene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating o-phenylenediethylene units.
